00:10:05.720 --> 00:10:11.960
[Guest 2]: The fact that that woman is not at home itself ensures that you would then hire a cook or a mate, right?

00:10:11.960 --> 00:10:18.720
[Guest 2]: So it's it's actually beneficial from the entire jobs angle also if not from just empower

00:10:18.720 --> 00:10:20.720
[Amit Varma]: Yeah, but those are low-skill jobs that you create

00:10:21.560 --> 00:10:27.640
[Guest 2]: But the idea is that then you create so then one more woman can then afford a household income that she will then use based

00:10:27.640 --> 00:10:29.720
[Guest 2]: On her usage. So the link is

00:10:30.360 --> 00:10:32.360
[Guest 2]: Actually positive. The only thing is that

00:10:32.760 --> 00:10:36.760
[Guest 2]: Other than being a cook, I think rest of them are still women oriented jobs

00:10:36.760 --> 00:10:41.960
[Guest 1]: You will still get a maid who's a woman you will still get a nanny a cleaning lady

